704072f-b.title: Brooklyn: Eastern Parkway - Utica Avenue
704072f-b.text:
Eastern arkway at the N.W. corner of Utica Avenue,
showing the East New York Savings Bank.
The crowd in front of the bank is worried about their
savings. The reason the bank is closed is because of President
Franklin D. Reosevelt's order closing all banks in the early
part of 1933. The bank could not be reopened until declafed
solvent by the Federal and State Bank Examiners.
About 1933
VViews 1 and 2
MAY BE RESROCUCED
